<br>
If anyone is interested in what my class (shadowknight) can and cannot do i am willing to give demonstrations, tutorials and also parsings once i figure out to do those silly parses.<br>
<br>
Was just that somone said warriors and sk have about 500hp difference.. that used to be true - me and my warrior friend - both human had 300hp difference between us. (most of that was because of the wepons he wielded)<br>
<br>
My main problem is that people keep throwing out information and some of it to me just seems out of date, false or biast. <br>
What i am hopeing to do is try show people it's not as bad as it sounds - yes i have read the steelwarrior boards when they first appeared.. i was starting to not play my warrior as much but made a new one and read there a fair bit and the amount of miss-information regarding knights was astounding - and resently i checked there resently and it's really just... sad.<br>
<br>
If this is any use to people i am lv64 with 29 AA spent - wich is not many.<br>
<br>
Runspeed 3/3<br>
Regen 3/3<br>
<br>
Combat fury 1/3<br>
Spell casting fury 1/3<br>
Combat agility 1/3<br>
Combat stability 1/3<br>
Natural duraibility 3/3<br>
<br>
Knights advantage 1/3<br>
Theft of life 2/3<br>
<br>
So if any warriors want to know the difference between a knight and warrior - or any other classes please give me a shout i will be happy go through some situations etc to cleer things up.<br>
<br>
